; Tests for the percent() function
; Calculates percentage: percent(amount, total) = (amount/total) * 100%

2012-01-01 Test percent function
    Assets:Test                       $100.00
    Equity:Opening

; Positive test: 50 out of 100 = 50%
test eval "percent(50, 100)"
50.00%
end test

; Positive test: 25 out of 100 = 25%
test eval "percent(25, 100)"
25.00%
end test

; Positive test: 1 out of 4 = 25%
test eval "percent(1, 4)"
25.00%
end test

; Negative test: too few arguments (requires two arguments)
test eval "percent(100)" -> 1
__ERROR__
While evaluating value expression:
  percent(100)
  ^^^^^^^^^^^^
While calling function 'percent 100':
Error: Too few arguments to function
end test
